article.headline: High Point 80, Longwood 68
article.story: FARMVILLE, Va. (AP) -- Arizona Reid scored 29 points and Mike Jefferson added 13 to lead High Point to an 80-68 win over Longwood on Saturday. A layup by Longwood's Dana Smith with 5:02 left in the first half tied the teams at 26, but Jefferson hit a layup just over a minute later to put High Point (3-3) ahead for good. The Panthers led 43-29 at the half. Kirk Williams led the Lancers (2-7) in scoring with 18 points, and Ryan Bogan added 16. High Point shot 50 percent from the field to Longwood's 43.3 percent, and outrebounded them 35-31.
